teacheasy.data

Class TextObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • teacheasy.data.PageObject
      • teacheasy.data.TextObject

  • public class TextObject
extends PageObject
    Encapsulates the data that describes a Text Object as defined in the TeachEasy digital lesson XML format. Extends the page object supertype.
    Version:
    1.0 05 Feb 2015
    Author:
    Daniel Berhe, Jake Ransom

      • TextObject

        public TextObject(float nXStart,
          float nYStart,
          float nXEnd,
          float nYEnd,
          java.lang.String nFont,
          int nFontSize,
          java.lang.String nColor,
          java.lang.String nSourceFile,
          float nDuration,
          float nStartTime)
        Constructor to create the data object with the data parsed from XML.
        Parameters:
        nXStart - Relative X axis start position (0 - 1).
        nYStart - Relative Y axis start position (0 - 1).
        nXEnd - Relative X axis end position (0 - 1).
        nYEnd - Relative Y axis end position (0 - 1).
        nFont - The font of the text box.
        nFontSize - The size of the text.
        nColor - The colour of the text in #AARRGGBB string format.
        nSourceFile - The source file path as a string.
        nDuration - The duration (not used).
        nStartTime - The start time (not used).
